The paper proposes a novel approach to model word significance and affinity within a document and in comparison to a large background corpus, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of t-SNE for generating a semantic word placement suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL).
